@startuml class_diagram

class Calculator {
    +add(a, b) : float
    +subtract(a, b) : float
    +multiply(a, b) : float
    +divide(a, b) : float
    +factorial(n: int) : int
}

note right of Calculator::divide
  Raises ZeroDivisionError
  when b == 0
end note

note right of Calculator::factorial
  Raises TypeError if n is bool
  or non-integer float.
  Raises ValueError if n < 0.
  Accepts float only when it
  represents an exact integer.
end note

@enduml
